{"kind":"article","sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-273-Meet-SwiftUI-spatial-layout","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"anchor":"overview","type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"😱 “No Overview Available!”","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Be the hero to change that by watching the video and providing notes! It’s super easy:","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","type":"reference"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Related-Sessions","type":"heading","text":"Related Sessions","level":2},{"style":"list","type":"links","items":["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-274-Better-together-SwiftUI-and-RealityKit","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC19-237-Building-Custom-Views-with-SwiftUI","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC22-10056-Compose-custom-layouts-with-SwiftUI"]}],"kind":"content"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Explore new tools for building spatial experiences using SwiftUI. Learn the basics of 3D SwiftUI views on visionOS, customize existing layouts with depth alignments, and use modifiers to rotate and position views in space. Discover how to use spatial containers to align views in the same 3D space, helping you create immersive and engaging apps."}],"sampleCodeDownload":{"action":{"overridingTitle":"Watch Video (20 min)","type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2025\/273","isActive":true},"kind":"sampleDownload"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25-273-meet-swiftui-spatial-layout"]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"roleHeading":"WWDC25","role":"sampleCode","title":"Meet SwiftUI spatial layout"},"references":{"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC25":{"title":"WWDC25","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Xcode 26, Swift 6.2, iOS\/macOS\/tvOS\/visionOS 26."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"New APIs: "},{"code":"Foundation Models","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"AlarmKit","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"PermissionKit","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", and more."}],"kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDC25-Icon.png"},{"type":"card","identifier":"WWDC25.jpg"}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25","role":"collectionGroup"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes":{"title":"WWDC Notes","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDCNotes.png"}],"role":"collection","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","abstract":[{"text":"Session notes shared by the community for the community.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic"},"WWDC25-Icon.png":{"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-Icon.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"alt":null,"identifier":"WWDC25-Icon.png","type":"image"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC22-10056-Compose-custom-layouts-with-SwiftUI":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC22-10056-Compose-custom-layouts-with-SwiftUI","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc22-10056-compose-custom-layouts-with-swiftui","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"SwiftUI now offers powerful tools to level up your layouts and arrange views for your app’s interface. We’ll introduce you to the Grid container, which helps you create highly customizable, two-dimensional layouts, and show you how you can use the Layout protocol to build your own containers with completely custom behavior. We’ll also explore how you can create seamless animated transitions between your layout types, and share tips and best practices for creating great interfaces.","type":"text"}],"kind":"article","title":"Compose custom layouts with SwiftUI","role":"sampleCode"},"https://wwdcnotes.com/documentation/wwdcnotes/contributing":{"titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn More…"}],"url":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","title":"Learn More…","type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing"},"WWDCNotes.png":{"type":"image","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDCNotes.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"identifier":"WWDCNotes.png","alt":null},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC19-237-Building-Custom-Views-with-SwiftUI":{"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc19-237-building-custom-views-with-swiftui","title":"Building Custom Views with SwiftUI","role":"sampleCode","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC19-237-Building-Custom-Views-with-SwiftUI","abstract":[{"text":"Learn how to build custom views and controls in SwiftUI with advanced composition, layout, graphics, and animation. See a demo of a high performance, animatable control and watch it made step by step in code. Gain a deeper understanding of the layout system of SwiftUI.","type":"text"}],"kind":"article","type":"topic"},"https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2025/273":{"checksum":null,"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2025\/273","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2025\/273","type":"download"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC25-274-Better-together-SwiftUI-and-RealityKit":{"type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"Discover how to seamlessly blend SwiftUI and RealityKit in visionOS 26. We’ll explore enhancements to Model3D, including animation and ConfigurationCatalog support, and demonstrate smooth transitions to RealityView. You’ll learn how to leverage SwiftUI animations to drive RealityKit component changes, implement interactive manipulation, use new SwiftUI components for richer interactions, and observe RealityKit changes from your SwiftUI code. We’ll also cover how to use unified coordinate conversion for cross-framework coordinate transformations.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25-274-better-together-swiftui-and-realitykit","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-274-Better-together-SwiftUI-and-RealityKit","role":"sampleCode","title":"Better together: SwiftUI and RealityKit"},"WWDC25.jpg":{"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25.jpg","traits":["1x","light"]}],"type":"image","alt":null,"identifier":"WWDC25.jpg"}}}